				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: well i was wonderin<a name="73602"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 23 05 1:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In my opinion.. for a level 18 , you are, in fact, doing it wrong.
<br />

<br />
That said... I bellow kited some myself in the past... and its DOG slow.
<br />

<br />
I would melee solo, twisting jonathans, hymn, denons, and if you can manage a 4 twist... chords.  This will get your melee skills up, offense, defense, dodge, and weapons.  You will want to get some decent weapons for this, fast is good. Hit the bazaar for that.  
<br />

<br />
If you are tight on cash, I like the goblin camps in butcherblock... 4 and a half plat from merchants per goblin head and per goblin blood.  Also the wandering greenbloods drop insignias that go for the same amount.  Spend a little time farming greens for cash if you need then get the weapons and kill blues elsewhere.
<br />

<br />
If you are well armored and motivated you can instrument twist at 18 for nice results.  Get 2 (or if you can handle it 3) mobs on ya.. Denons with horn... chords with lute...hymn with lute.. and repeat.  Its like mini AOE kiting, with the exception that you are tanking rather than kiting.  This method has some downtime between, but killing 3 at once is nice.  Have Bellow memmed for when you get down to 1 and its runnin.  Warning!!! you must train up your brass skill before attempting this or missed notes galore on denons (I assume your string skill is OK... if not train it up too.
<br />

<br />
Regarding swarm kiting... I wouldn't try it at 27.  At 27 charm kite 1 on 1.  Learn how to use that charm well.  In fact keep at that til level 30.  Then you will have fufils, and can chant/bellow your ex-pet down rather than just bellowing it down.
<br />

<br />
Good hunting to ya...
<br />
Reys</span></td>
